cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper deals with designing a modular neural network architecture for joint depth prediction and semantic segmentation, which are both computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the cross-modality influence between the two tasks, which involves analyzing the relationship between different network design choices, indicating a possible connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the proposed architecture involves fusing the results of the two tasks, which could be relevant to cs.RO (Robotics) as well. Finally, the paper deals with neural networks, which is a topic that falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
